cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the use of Linked Data in the cultural heritage sector, which involves information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL) as well as databases (DB). The paper also touches on artificial intelligence (AI) and the philosophical nature of identity, which are relevant to the sub-category of cybernetics (CY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.DL, and cs.DB, followed by cs.AI and cs.CY.
